      "message": "nit, nothing to change in this CL: `string_view + string_view` isn\u0027t something that would work with normal C++17 std::string_views. A string_view doesn\u0027t support any form of concatenation; you need to explicitly convert it into a string first.\n\nhttps://godbolt.org/z/4jevasMcW\n\nI\u0027m not too worried about it. For that matter, it might be possible to just continue providing this overload even if/when we transition to the standard types. There might be a rule against it (messing with standard library types is sometimes UB?), but I didn\u0027t see anything forbidding it on brief inspection, and it seems to work in practice:\n\nhttps://godbolt.org/z/aGn5971bj\n\nAt any rate, we can always fix this up in the future if it becomes an issue. I don\u0027t see a problem with it for this CL.",
